cli\u003eblack myrobalan\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003ebelleric myrobalan\u003c/li\u003e"},{"tagName":"p","source":"This compound is known to have fat-reducing properties and has been found in a \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"PubMed Central\" rationale=\"Highly respected database from the National Institutes of Health\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23251942/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-1xhnmo5\"\u003e2012 animal study\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e to reduce fat and cholesterol levels. Since lipomas are believed to form as a result of an overgrowth of fat cells, this treatment and similar compounds used in Ayurvedic medicine seek to address the cause of these tumors. "},{"tagName":"p","source":"However, it should be noted that the fat cells that make up lipomas are a different type of fat cells unaffected by weight loss, fat reduction, or lower cholesterol levels."},{"tagName":"p","source":"In some cases, Ayurveda does recommend excision, or the cutting out of the lipoma. This similar to the surgical removal methods used in Western medicine."},{"tagName":"h3","source":"Risks to note"},{"tagName":"p","source":"While there may not be recommendations against using Ayruvedic treatments in the United States, they are suggested only as a complementary therapy to standard care. Some concerns with Ayurveda include:"},{"tagName":"ul","source":"\u003cli\u003erisk of delaying urgent medical treatment\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003etoxicity of certain medication compounds\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003elack of regulation on providers and practices\u003c/li\u003e"},{"tagName":"p","source":"If you’re interested in trying Ayurveda as a complementary therapy, be sure to tell a healthcare professional exactly what therapies you are using."}]},{"id":"seeking-medical-care","title":"Seeking medical care","isCollapsable":false,"header":["When to seek medical care"],"body":[{"tagName":"p","attributes":{"className":"standout--body"},"source":"While lipomas are often painless, harmless growths, this isn’t always the case. It can be difficult to accurately diagnose a growth under your skin without removing it for inspection — or at least taking a biopsy. A \u003ca href=\"https://www.healthline.com/health/biopsy\" class=\"content-link css-1xhnmo5\"\u003ebiopsy\u003c/a\u003e is a procedure where a healthcare professional removes a piece of tissue and sends it to a lab to be examined."},{"tagName":"p","attributes":{"className":"standout--body"},"source":"There’s a risk that what you think is a harmless lipoma could actually be a more serious growth or tumor."},{"tagName":"p","source":"You should seek medical care as soon as possible if your growth:"},{"tagName":"ul","source":"\u003cli\u003ehas color changes in the skin around it\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003ebecomes warm or hot\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003echanges in size\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003echanges in color\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eincreases in density or hardness\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003ecauses increased pain\u003c/li\u003e"}]},{"id":"bottom-line","title":"Bottom line","isCollapsable":false,"header":["The bottom line"],"body":[{"tagName":"p","source":"Lipomas are mostly harmless growths that usually only pose a cosmetic concern. There is little data on alternative medicine strategies like Ayurveda to treat your lipoma. "},{"tagName":"p","source":"Ayurveda practices can’t replace standard care for lipomas, but they may act as a complementary therapy."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Discuss any plans for trying alternative medicine with your doctor. They can also make sure your lipoma isn’t something more serious so that you don’t delay standard care, if needed."}]}],"hasAffiliateLinks":false,"affiliates":[],"propsFor":{"articleResources":[{"displayLink":"hopkinsmedicine.org/health/wellness-and-prevention/ayurveda","link":"https://www.hopkinsmedicine.org/health/wellness-and-prevention/ayurveda#:~:text=Ayurveda%2C%20a%20natur